iche|publisher=Myjuve.it}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://juworld.net/stagioni-riepilogo.asp?idstagione=35|title=Statistiche|publisher=Juworld.net}}\n\n{{Juventus F.C.}}\n{{Juventus F.C. seasons}}\n{{1931\u201332 in Italian football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1931-32 Juventus F.C. season}}\n[[Category:Juventus F.C. seasons]]\n[[Category:Scudetto-winning seasons]]\n\n\n{{Italy-sport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club season\n|club = [[Juventus|Foot-Ball Club Juventus]]\n|season = 1931-32\n|manager = [[Carlo Carcano]]\n|chairman = [[Edoardo Agnelli]]\n|chrtitle= President\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|league = [[Serie A]]\n|league result = [[1931-32 Serie A|1\u00ba]] (in [[1932 Mitropa Cup|Mitropa Cup]])\n|cup1 = [[Mitropa Cup]]\n|cup1 result = [[1932 Mitropa Cup|Semifinals]]\n|league topscorer = [[Raimundo Orsi]] (20)\n|season topscorer = [[Raimundo Orsi|Orsi]] (23)\n\n|pattern_la1 = _juve2\n|leftarm1 = ffffff\n|pattern_b1 =_juve193236h\n|body1 = ffffff\n|pattern_ra1 = _juve2\n|rightarm1 = ffffff\n|shorts1 = ffffff\n|pattern_so1 = _juve\n|socks1 = 000000\n\n|prevseason = [[1930\u201331 F.B.C. Juventus season|1930-31]]\n|nextseason = [[1932\u201333 F.B.C. Juventus season|1932-33]]\n}}\n\nDuring the 1931\u201332 season '''Foot-Ball Club Juventus''' competed in Serie A and Mitropa Cup.\n\n==Summary==\nThe club transferred new players in to the roster such as [[Enzo Rosa]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://myjuve.com/player/172914/|title=Enzo Rosa signed with Juventus|publisher=myjuve.com}}</ref> and Brazilian [[Pietro Sernagiotto]] (who had  an agreement with Genova).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttojuve.com/?action=read&idnotizia=12096|title=Sernagiotto|publisher=tuttojuve.com}}</ref> Juventus clinched its second title in a row with 54 points<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/ital32.html|publisher=RSSSF.com|title=Season 1931-32}}</ref> one more from the previous campaign surpassing runner-up Bologna thanks to a powerful offense scoring 89 goals (65 in away) and conceded only 38.\n\nAlso [[Raimundo Orsi]] with 20 goals (included 5 penalties) became 5th best topscorer of the league.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juworld.net/stagioni-partite-amichevoli.asp?idstagione=35|publisher=juworld.net|title= Orsi goals season|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\n== Squad ==\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=GK|nat=ITA|name=[[Gianpiero Combi]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Umberto Caligaris]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Ferrero]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Virginio Rosetta]]}}(Captain)\n{{fs player|no=|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Varglien]]}} II\n{{fs player|no=|pos=DF|nat=ITA|name=[[Luigi Bertolini]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=MF|nat=ARG|name=[[Luis Monti]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=MF|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Varglien]]}} I\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=MF|nat=ARG|name=[[Renato Cesarini]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=MF|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Ferrari]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=FW|nat=ARG|name=[[Juan Maglio|Juan Jos\u00e9 Maglio]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Federico Munerati]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=FW|nat=ARG|name=[[Raimundo Orsi]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Enzo Rosa]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=FW|nat=BRA|name=[[Pietro Sernagiotto]]}}\n{{fs player|no=|pos=FW|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Vecchina]]}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Serie A ===\n{{main|1931-32 Serie A}}\n\n====League table====\n{{:1931-32 Serie A|showteam=JUV}}\n\n====Matches====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=20 September 1931\n|time=15:30\n|round=1\n|team1=Pro Patria\n|team2=Juventus\n|score=1-1\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1931/625/\n|location=[[Busto Arsizio]]\n|stadium=Stadio Comunale\n|atttendance=\n|referee=Bertoli\n|goals1=[[Gastone Cazzaniga|Cazzaniga]] {{goal|75}}\n|goals2={{goal|40}} [[Luis Monti|Monti]]\n|result=D\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=27 September 1931\n|time=\n|round=2\n|team1=Juventus\n|team2=[[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]]\n|score=5-3\