 goal:\n*{{Flagicon|ITA|1861}} [[Enzo Rosa]]\n*{{Flagicon|ITA|1861}} {{Flagicon|BRA|1889}} [[Pietro Sernagiotto]]\n*{{Flagicon|ITA|1861}} [[Giovanni Varglien]]\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.myjuve.it/stagione-1931-32-juventus/dettaglio-36.aspx|title=Statistiche|publisher=Myjuve.it}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://juworld.net/stagioni-riepilogo.asp?idstagione=35|title=Statistiche|publisher=Juworld.net}}\n\n{{Juventus F.C.}}\n{{Juventus F.C. seasons}}\n{{1931\u201332 in Italian football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1931-32 Juventus F.C. season}}\n[[Category:Juventus F.C. seasons]]\n[[Category:Italian football clubs 1931\u201332 season|Juventus]]\n[[Category:Scudetto-winning seasons]]\n\n\n{{Italy-sport-stub}}\n", "name_user": "TheImaCow", "label": "safe", "comment": "removedCategory:Italian football clubs 1931\u201332 seasonusingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1931%E2%80%9332_F.B.C._Juventus_season"}
{"title_page": "Goran Ljubojevi\u0107", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Goran Ljubojevi\u0107\n| image               =\n| image_size          = 300px\n| caption             = Ljubojevi\u0107 playing for [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1983|5|4}}\n| birth_place         = [[Osijek]], [[Socialist Federative Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.89|abbr=on}}\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub         = Retired\n| clubnumber          = \n| youthyears1         =           |youthclubs1 = [[NK Osijek|Osijek]]\n| years1              = 2001\u20132004 |clubs1  = [[NK Osijek|Osijek]]                   |caps1 =  64 |goals1 = 23\n| years2              = 2004\u20132006 |clubs2  = [[Dinamo Zagreb]]                      |caps2 =  41 |goals2 = 13\n| years3              = 2006      |clubs3  = \u2192 [[FC St. Gallen|St. Gallen]] (loan)  |caps3 =  17 |goals3 = 5\n| years4              = 2006\u20132009 |clubs4  = [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]]                   |caps4 =  38 |goals4 = 12\n| years5              = 2009\u20132010 |clubs5  = [[NK Zagreb]]                          |caps5 =  12 |goals5 = 6\n| years6              = 2010\u20132011 |clubs6  = [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]]                    |caps6 =  11 |goals6 = 2\n| years7              = 2011\u20132012 |clubs7  = [[NK Osijek|Osijek]]                   |caps7 =  25 |goals7 = 6\n| years8              = 2012      |clubs8  = [[FCM T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219|T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219]]        |caps8 =  9  |goals8 = 5\n| years9              = 2012\u20132013 |clubs9  = [[Naft Tehran]]                        |caps9 =  11 |goals9 = 4\n| years10             = 2013\u20132014 |clubs10 = [[NK Osijek|Osijek]]                   |caps10 = 8  |goals10 = 6\n| years11             = 2014\u20132015 |clubs11 = [[Balestier Khalsa]]                   |caps11 = 27 |goals11 = 20\n| years12             = 2015\u20132016 |clubs12 = [[Sriwijaya FC|Sriwijaya]]             |caps12 = 9  |goals12 = 3\n| years13             = 2016      |clubs13 = [[NK Vinogradar|Vinogradar]]           |caps13 = 15 |goals13 = 10\n| years14             = 2017      |clubs14 = [[NK Trnje|Trnje]]                     |caps14 = 9  |goals14 = 2\n| nationalyears1      = 1998\u20131999 |nationalteam1 = Croatia U15\n| nationalcaps1       = 6         |nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalyears2      = 1999\u20132000 |nationalteam2 = Croatia U16\n| nationalcaps2       = 7         |nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3      = 1999      |nationalteam3 = [[Croatia national under-17 football team|Croatia U17]]\n| nationalcaps3       = 3         |nationalgoals3 = 1\n| nationalyears4      = 2000\u20132001 |nationalteam4 = [[Croatia national under-19 football team|Croatia U19]]\n| nationalcaps4       = 10        |nationalgoals4 = 7\n| nationalyears5      = 2001\u20132003 |nationalteam5 = [[Croatia national under-20 football team|Croatia U20]]\n| nationalcaps5       = 6         |nationalgoals5 = 2\n| nationalyears6      = 2003\u20132005 |nationalteam6 = [[Croatia national under-21 football team|Croatia U21]]\n| nationalcaps6       = 18        |nationalgoals6 = 3\n| pcupdate            = 21:26, 11 July 2017 (UTC)\n| ntupdate            = \n}}\n\n'''Goran Ljubojevi\u0107''' ({{IPA-sh|\u0261\u01d2ran \u028eub\u01d2\u02d0je\u028bit\u0255|hr}}; born 4 May 1983) is a retired Croatian footballer who last played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[NK Trnje]].<ref>[http://sportnews.hr/index.php/3-hnl/3-hnl-zapad/927-trnje-i-maksimir-skroz-miroljubivo-1-1-spudic-skinuo-zicer-maksimiru-ljubojevic-iskusavali-smo-nove-sustave-ali-nije-bilo-bas-najbolje-trnje-na-more-maksimir-u-veslacku.html Ljubojevi\u0107: Isku\u0161avali smo nove sustave, ali nije bilo ba\u0161 najbolje]\u201a sportnews.hr, 15 February 2017</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n\nAs one of the best young national team players, he was transferred at the end of August 2006 from [[Dinamo Zagreb]] to KRC Genk. He also played for [[NK Osijek]] and [[FC St. Gallen]].\n\nIn the 2006\u201307 season, he earned a season record of five goals in five following games. In total, he made 11 goals for KRC Genk, according to his playing time he was the most efficient scorer in the Belgian [[Belgian First Division A|Jupiler League]] of that season.\n\nIn December 2009, he turned a new page in his career by signing with [[NK Zagreb]]. He scored six goals in a half season. This opened the eyes of several teams who were interested in this targetstriker. [[Odense]] and [[AIK Stockholm|AIK]] showed the most interest. Finally, AIK signed him in July 2010.\n\n\"Ljubo\" also was a member of the Croatian national team under 21. His highlight was a victory over England on 13 August 2003, which Croatia won by 0\u20133. Ljubojevi\u0107 scored the first two goals and delivered the assist for the third goal.\n\nIn 2014, he joined [[Balestier Khalsa]] as their first ever marquee signing. He scored the first goal in the [[2014 Singapore Cup]] on 7 November 2014 and the club's maiden win in the [[Singapore Cup]]. He ended the season as a club top scorer with 27 goals.\n\nHe last played for [[NK Trnje]] based in the city of [[Zagreb]].\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Balestier Khalsa'''\n* [[Singapore Cup]]: [[2014 Singapore Cup|2014]]\n\n\u2018\u2019\u2019KRC GENK\u2019\u2019\u2019\n* [[Beker van Belgie]]: [[2009 Beker van Belgie|2009]]\n\n\u2018\u2019\u2019DINAMO ZAGREB\u2019\u2019\u2019\n* [[Croatian League Champions]]: 2005\u20132006\n\n===Individual===\n* Top goalscorers by season of Balestier Khalsa: 2014\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{CFF player|6169/goran-ljubojevic}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n\n{{Croatian Football Hope of the Year award}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ljubojevic, Goran}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Osijek]]\n[[Category:Croatian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association fo