rthy (2012).\n\n==Variants==\n* '''F.15''' - prototype with [[Lycoming O-320]] engine and three seats (1 built)\n* '''F.15A''' - initial production version with [[Lycoming O-360]] engine and four seats (10 built by [[Procaer]])\n[[File:Procaer F.15B Picchio I-GIMO Linate 31.07.65ras034 edited-3.jpg|thumb|right|Procaer F.15B Picchio at [[Milan Linate Airport]] in 1965]]\n* '''F.15B''' - similar to F.15A but with larger-span wings and fuel tanks relocated from fuselage to wings (20 built by Procaer)\n* '''F.15C''' - version with [[Continental Motors Company|Continental IO-470]] engine and tip tanks (1 built)\n* '''F.15D''' - proposed version similar to F.15B with [[Franklin Engine Company|Franklin]] engine (not built)\n* '''F.15E''' - all-metal version of F.15B with [[Continental IO-520]]K engine (2 built I-PROM I-PROD by [[Procaer]])\n* '''F.15F Delfino''' - two-seat version of F.15E with bubble canopy (1 built I-PROL by Procaer )\n** '''F.15F Excalibur''' - F.15F built by [[JSC Sokol]] for [[HOAC]]\n<!-- ==Units using this aircraft/Operators (choose)== -->\n\n==Specifications (F.15B) ==\n{{Aircraft specs\n|ref=Jane's All The World's Aircraft 1961\u201362<ref name=\"JAWA61 p107-8\">{{Harvnb|Taylor|1961|pp=107\u2013108}}</ref>\n|prime units?=met\n<!--\n        General characteristics\n-->\n|genhide= \n\n|crew=1\n|capacity=3 passengers\n|length m=7.50\n|length ft=\n|length in=\n|span m=9.90\n|span ft=\n|span in=\n|height m=2.80\n|height ft=\n|height in=\n|wing area sqm=13.30\n|wing area sqft=\n|aspect ratio=7.37:1\n|airfoil=NACA 64.215/64.210\n|empty weight kg=695\n|empty weight lb=\n|gross weight kg=1150\n|gross weight lb=\n|fuel capacity={{convert|125|L|USgal impgal|abbr=on}}\n<!--\n        Powerplant\n-->\n|eng1 number=1\n|eng1 name=[[Lycoming O-360]]-A1A\n|eng1 type=horizontally opposed, four-cylinder, air-cooled piston engine\n|eng1 kw=<!-- prop engines -->\n|eng1 hp=180<!-- prop engines -->\n\n|prop blade number=<!-- propeller aircraft -->\n|prop name=\n|prop dia