. Juventus season|1931-32]]\n}}\nDuring the 1930-31 '''Foot-Ball Club Juventus''' played in Serie A and Mitropa Cup.\n\n== Summary ==\nThe team competed in its second [[Serie A]] with sole group format, and clinched  the  title. The club replaced Scottish couch [[Billy Aitken]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.storiedicalcio.altervista.org/sfide_juventus_roma.html|publisher=storiedicalcio.altervista.org|title=Aitken}}</ref> with former Italian National Team manager [[Carlo Carcano]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/27-10-2015/hall-of-fame-vialli-mancini-facchetti-ronaldo-herrera-agnelli-tardelli-ferlaino-130676725232.shtml|title=Legend Carcano|publisher=gazzetta.it}}</ref> introducing ''Metodo'' tactic (2-3-2-3) with the defenders trio Combi-Rosetta-Caligaris (one of all-time best defenders line up).\n\nThe club renforced the block with [[Alfredo Bodoira]] and [[Umberto Ghibaudo]]. In midfield arrived argentinen [[Eugenio Castellucci]], also [[Francesco Rier]] and [[Aldo Vollono]], on attack from Argentina [[Jos\u00e9 Maglio]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.once-onze.narod.ru/ARGENTINA/M/Mab/Maglio_Juan_Jose.mht|title=Maglio comes to Juve|language=Italian|publisher=once-onze.narod.ru}}</ref> along with Giovanni Ferrari, Gilberto Pogliano et Giovanni Vecchina.\n\n== Squad ==\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Alfredo Bodoira]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Gianpiero Combi]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Umberto Ghibaudo]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Ezio Sclavi]]|pos=MF}}<ref>Added for Mitropa Cup.</ref>\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Umberto Caligaris]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Ferrero]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Luis Monti]]|pos=DF}}<ref> Added </ref>\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Virginio Rosetta]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Varglien|Varglien II]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Oreste Barale]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Luigi Bertolini]]|pos=MF}}<ref> Added </ref>\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Carlo Bigatto]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=[[Eugenio Castellucci]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Carlo Crotti]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Lino Mosca]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Francesco Rier]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Varglien|Varglien I]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Aldo Vollono]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Renato Cesarini]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Ferrari]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=[[Jos\u00e9 Maglio]]|pos=FW}}<ref> Added </ref>\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Federico Munerati]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Raimundo Orsi]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Gilberto Pogliano]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Vecchina]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Oliviero Vojak|Vojak II]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Serie A ===\n{{main|1930-31 Serie A}}\n====League table====\n{{:1930-31 Serie A|showteam=JUV}}\n\n==== Matches ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 28 September 1930\n|round = 1\n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = Pro Patria\n|score = 4-1\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1930/313/\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Campo Juventus]]\n|attendance =\n|referee= Giusto Sardi\n|goals1 = [[Renato Cesarini|Cesarini]] {{Goal|1}}<br/>[[Giovanni Vecchina|Vecchina]] {{Goal|31||75||84}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|77}} [[Giovanni Colombo (calciatore 1905)|Colombo I]]\n|result = W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 5 October 1930\n|round = 2\n|time = \n|team1 = [[A.C. Milan|Milan]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 0-3\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1930/423/\n|location = Milano\n|stadium = [[Stadio Giuseppe Meazza|Campo San Siro]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Giuseppe Turbiani\n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = {{Goal|4||73}} [[Federico Munerati|Munerati]]<br/>{{Goal|78}} [[Ra